headline: Is It Too Late To Consider Ralph Lauren (RL) After A 55% One Year Surge?
summary: If you are wondering whether Ralph Lauren’s share price still reflects good value after a strong run, this article will walk you through what the numbers actually say. The stock last closed at US$363.25, with returns of 1.3% over 7 days, a 1.9% decline over 30 days, a small 0.2% gain year to date, and a 55.5% return over 1 year. The 3 year and 5 year returns sit at 222.5% and 265.2% respectively. These moves have come alongside ongoing brand activity and broader market attention on premium...
